<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Best Class</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Fanaeb">Fanaeb</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 10:17 a.m. 2/6/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Best Class<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>About those comments below, I have to say that most of those comments are valid only to the writer. Most classes with the exception of Wizards and maybe a few others, are capable of playing several different ways. My Druid for example, has a few cure spells, a few damage spells, a few buff spells. some others. I can play almost any angle in a battle. The same goes for most spell casters. Wizards can be quite cheap but that depends on your style of play. Most classes are difficult to play but when handled well, any class could easily defeat another. I all depends on your style.

</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
